The paper deals with decentralized detection in a sensor network with communication constraints, specifically a bandwidth constraint. This suggests that the paper may fall under the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. Additionally, the use of direct-sequence code-division multiple-access (DS-CDMA) implies a focus on networking and communication, which could also place the paper in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The use of random matrix theory to derive asymptotic performance suggests a focus on mathematical modeling and analysis, which could place the paper in the Machine Learning (cs.MM) or Learning (cs.LG) categories.
